Vice President Pence and Prime Minister Netanyahu met at the American Embassy in Jerusalem to discuss regional issues and plans for the future. Pence congratulated Netanyahu on the successful commemoration of the 75th anniversary of the liberation of Auschwitz, where 49 nations stood in solidarity against anti-Semitism. Pence also extended an invitation to Netanyahu and Benny Gantz, leader of the Blue and White Party, to visit the White House to discuss regional issues and the prospect of peace. Netanyahu expressed gratitude for the friendship and support of President Trump and accepted the invitation to Washington. The meeting concluded with Ambassador Dermer presenting Pence and Netanyahu with flags that flew over the United States Embassy in Jerusalem.